NIWA-SCENZ Timeseries imagery services (IS)

A collection of timesteps of MODIS products, where each 500 square meter pixel is summarised (median) into timeseries by week (52 yr-1), month (12 yr-1), season (4 yr-1), and year (July-2002 to present). Please refer to the "Details" and "Versions" tabs for more comprehensive information on satellite remote sensing data, imagery services, product versioning, and updates.  Here, we describe how to use this ArcGIS Web Application.  The app defaults to a single product timestep to ensure efficient loading.

 

General


Busy loading: When the “loading wheel” is spinning (bottom right) try not to change view, by scrolling or zooming in or out with mouse, as this will result in multiple views stacking up, pending exporting images to be loaded on the screen. Some actions take time depending on complexity of selection and number of layers to load. Reload the webpage if necessary.

Navigation widgets


Search (Find address or place):   Enter a place of interest and select. Accepts GPS Latitude and Longitude coordinates (e.g. -41.27, 174.85). This is an efficient alternative to navigating with mouse or keyboard, avoiding multiple loading of images as the user pans/zooms to area of interest.


Zoom Slider:  Alternative to using mouse wheel or keyboard for zooming.


Home:  Web map’s default extent to include the entire New Zealand image layer.


My location:  If you have location services enabled in your web browser, the web map will reposition and highlight your location.


Full screen: Maximise your screen-a-state!


Extent navigate (previous and next): Navigate through extents from session. 

Sidebar widgets


Renderer (use with Filter): A series of product specific renderings to bracket both spatial and seasonal ranges for the entire coverage (defaults to CHL). If you use “Stretch” or “None” all products will be loaded, so use prior to Filter to select a product to display. For best results with stretch parameters, select dynamic range adjustment (DRA) with either a standard deviation or percentage clip. If you select a different product render, make sure either “Filter” product is off or selected to correct product otherwise it will not show.


Filter (use with Renderer):  Filters for product, timestep, year and month. All filters are ON by default to load a single layer. Turning OFF a filter loads all available items, stacking one on top of the other (depending on which other filters are on), so use with caution as it may take some time to load. Change IS Renderer to product or "Stretch" to render using this widget. Stretch allows product selection from here. If product filter is turned OFF while on “Stretch”, all products will be loaded.


Selector (use with other widgets): Selects a single image based on the date and provides either a slider (default) or drop-down list to allow selection. The configuration of Filter determines the images available. “Set current as secondary layer” is used in conjunction with Swipe for comparing with another product or time. Disable before closing.


Swipe (use with Selector): First use Selector to set a product image of interest as a secondary layer (Layer: Product – Date). Then whatever product image the webpage is on (Layer: Product), can be used to vertically swipe compare to the secondary layer. These can be seen in the Layer List. To maximise gradient discrimination use on Renderer on “Stretch” DRA – both images will dynamically adjust colour scaling.


Profile (Product vs Time): Extracts data values for an individual pixel (“Identify”) or a timeseries plot (“Temporal profile”). Dependant on Filter as to what timesteps, years and month are extracted and plotted.

Header widgets


Basemaps (NZTM selection):  User preference. Some are better at different zoom levels and with different product renderings.


Layers (with legends): Active product layer, secondary (temporary) layer, other layers added using Add Data, and basemap, with associated legends. Several viewing and order options are available in the three-dot icon.


eDraw (point, line, polygon):  A community user extension of the standard draw widget with additional features to show measurements, change look, name, save and export/import.  On selection of an area of interest (polygon), use the three-dot icon to “set as input” for the various timesteps (weeks, months, seasons, or years) for Export. The point and line drawing modes are not exportable as these are not polygons.


Export (polygon input from eDraw):  A series of geo-processing tools which extracts all products, from all layers (dates from mid-2002 - present), from all pixels within the polygon input area (eDraw). “Run” from appropriate timestep, without adding an “Output Feature Service Name”, and when completed a link appears in the output tab. Selecting the link will download a file “*.csv” to your computer. Rename the file and use for further analysis in other software. Monthly timestep extractions can be analysed further on the Shiny-SCENZ (Monthly) page.  Download times will depend on the size of the polygon and may “fail” if too large. Be patient.


Add Data (search online, url, file):  You can search within or outside your organisation, If adding “fails” it is likely to be on a different projection to NZTM.  The “Layers” icon at the bottom right organises load layers for easy removal.


Bookmarks (main Islands and user):  Main islands (permanent) and user added bookmarks that should remain is using same computer and web-browser. Use with Search (Find address or place), adjust map (zoom and pan), then “Add” bookmark and save a name.


Share (link to app): Share a link or embed this app in a website, with a range of options for display.


Print (imagery layer): Various options of layout and format to save (print) to a file of choice (e.g. PDF, png, tiff).


Export (imagery layer):  NOT WORKING YET.  Should export (save to portal or disk) the current layer, either entirely, or define the extent.


About (Web app): Specifically, about this Web application.


  
Product version: ArcGIS Web AppBuilder (Developer Edition) 2.19
Kernel version: 2.19
